article.description: McKinney scores 23, Sacramento St. beats Montana St. 75-59
article.headline: McKinney scores 23, Sacramento St. beats Montana St. 75-59
article.linkText: McKinney scores 23, Sacramento St. beats Montana St. 75-59
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Mikh McKinney had 23 points and eight assists, and Dylan Garrity scored 18 on Thursday night to help Sacramento State pull away from Montana State for a 75-59 win. Nick Hornsby added 12 points and seven rebounds for Sacramento State (14-6, 8-1 Big Sky), which has won five in a row and 9 of 10. The first eight minutes of the second half included three ties and three lead changes before McKinney's jumper -- which started a 10-2 run -- with 11 minutes left gave the Hornets the lead, 46-44, for good. Stephan Holm and Marcus Colbert hit 3-pointers 39 seconds apart to keep Montana State (4-16, 1-7) within five with six minutes remaining, but a layup by McKinney sparked a 16-3 spurt that gave Sacramento State a 73-55 lead with 1:24 to play. The Hornets made 14 of 24 (58 percent) field goals, including 4 of 8 from 3-point range, in the second half. Colbert led Montana State with 13 points.
